OL,7,FThis means that as we progress through
OL,8,Fthe summer, the ground stores up heat
OL,9,Fand August temperatures benefit from
OL,10,Fthis cumulative heating effect.
OL,12,FOur sea also tends to be at its
OL,13,Fwarmest in August, with an average
OL,14,Ftemperature of around 18C.
OL,16,FThis can amplify our warmer land
OL,17,Ftemperatures in August by reducing the
OL,18,Fcooling effect of sea breezes.
